 We suggest that the presence or absence of an extended envelope\nin {\\em very young clusters} may be due to the gas distribution of the\nproto-cluster giant molecular cloud, in particular if the proto-cluster core\nbecomes distinct from the surrounding gas before star formation begins.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 Feb 2013 09:55:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-12"}
